text.section:
A person who has not been licensed by the Board may, after having notified the county board of health, install a temporary dewatering device to facilitate the installation of underground utilities if the device:
Is installed 30 feet or less below the ground surface;
Is not located in any trench used for the installation of underground utilities;
Contains no mechanical pumping equipment below the surface; and
Is removed no more than 30 days after installation.
